Properties

  • Edit
    EndTime
    EndTime

    Gets or sets the time at which the start task stopped running.

    [JsonProperty(PropertyName = "endTime")]
public DateTime? EndTime { get; set; }<JsonProperty(PropertyName:="endTime")>
Public Property EndTime As Date?

    Property Value

    • Nullable<DateTime>
      Nullable(Of DateTime)

    Remarks

    This is the end time of the most recent run of the start task, if that run has completed (even if that run failed and a retry is pending). This element is not present if the start task is currently running.

  • Edit
    ExitCode
    ExitCode

    Gets or sets the exit code of the program specified on the start task command line.

    [JsonProperty(PropertyName = "exitCode")]
public int ? ExitCode { get; set; }<JsonProperty(PropertyName:="exitCode")>
Public Property ExitCode As Integer?

    Property Value

    • Nullable<Int32>
      Nullable(Of Int32)

    Remarks

    This property is set only if the start task is in the completed state. In general, the exit code for a process reflects the specific convention implemented by the application developer for that process. If you use the exit code value to make decisions in your code, be sure that you know the exit code convention used by the application process. However, if the Batch service terminates the start task (due to timeout, or user termination via the API) you may see an operating system-defined exit code.

  • Edit
    LastRetryTime
    LastRetryTime

    Gets or sets the most recent time at which a retry of the task started running.

    [JsonProperty(PropertyName = "lastRetryTime")]
public DateTime? LastRetryTime { get; set; }<JsonProperty(PropertyName:="lastRetryTime")>
Public Property LastRetryTime As Date?

    Property Value

    • Nullable<DateTime>
      Nullable(Of DateTime)

    Remarks

    This element is present only if the task was retried (i.e. retryCount is nonzero). If present, this is typically the same as startTime, but may be different if the task has been restarted for reasons other than retry; for example, if the compute node was rebooted during a retry, then the startTime is updated but the lastRetryTime is not.

Public Property RetryCount As Integer

    Property Value

      Int32

    Remarks

    The task is retried if it exits with a nonzero exit code, up to the specified MaxTaskRetryCount.

Public Property StartTime As Date

    Property Value

    • DateTime
      DateTime

    Remarks

    State
    State

    Gets or sets the state of the start task on the compute node.

    [JsonProperty(PropertyName = "state")]
public StartTaskState State { get; set; }<JsonProperty(PropertyName:="state")>
Public Property State As StartTaskState

    Property Value

    • StartTaskState
      StartTaskState

    Remarks

    running - The start task is currently running. completed - The start task has exited with exit code 0, or the start task has failed and the retry limit has reached, or the start task process did not run due to scheduling errors. Possible values include: 'running', 'completed'
